news.title: Noida administration meets lift makers over maintenance costs under new act
news.para: ​​Residents complained that since the act mandates manufacturers to provide maintenance, the lift makers have increased their prices.

news.title: Bombay HC declares Supreme Construction's director arrest illegal over violation of rights
news.para: The Chembur police, Taloja police station, and CBD Belapur police station registered cases of cheating against Lalit Tekchandani of Supreme Builders.

news.title: Delhi: NGT seeks response on illegal sand mining in Yamuna floodplain
news.para: A bench of NGT Chairperson Justice Prakash Shrivastava and expert member A Senthil Vel had taken a suo motu (on its own) cognisance of a newspaper report on the large-scale illegal mining in the floodplain between Alipur in north Delhi and Panchayara in Ghaziabad.

news.title: Noida authority seals 27 unsold flats of Skytech Matrott over Rs 30 crore dues
news.para: Consequently, the Authority sealed 27 unsold flats in the project on the directions of its chief executive officer Lokesh M. Earlier, in September, the Authority sealed five flats in the same project for non-compliance.

news.title: Gujarat CM reviews over 5,000 suggestions on proposed jantri rates
news.para: Official sources said that the govt is not inclined to extend the deadline for submitting suggestions or objections to the proposal beyond Jan 20, 2025, and that the number of objections is likely to exceed 10,000.

news.title: Developers get notices from GST authorities over Rs 3,500 crore input tax credit claims
news.para: These notices follow a Supreme Court ruling in October concerning Safari Retreats that allowed commercial realty companies to claim input tax credit (ITC) on construction cost for rental buildings.

news.title: Lucknow: ED searches 16 premises associated with Kalpataru Group
news.para: During searches, ED officials seized unexplained cash amounting to Rs over 1 crore, sale deeds/documents of 88 immovable properties, and digital/electronic evidence of hundreds of properties related to the case.

news.title: ITC acquires 2.44% stake in EIH and 0.53% in Leela hospitality chains
news.para: "The company today acquired 2.44 per cent of the share capital (comprising 1.52 crore equity shares of Rs 2 each) of EIH and 0.53 per cent of the share capital (comprising 34.60 lakh equity shares of Rs 2 each) of HLV from RCL," ITC said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Traders protest over hike in property tax, electricity tariff in Tamil Nadu
news.para: As part of the strike, grocery stores, restaurants, bakeries, textile shops, jewellery stores, cellphone shops and electrical shops remained shut. Around 300 shops in the Tirupur cotton market complex and vegetable market also remained closed.

news.title: Manish Paul rents out office space for Rs 2 lakh per month in Mumbai
news.para: The leased property spans 1,200 sq ft (~111.48 sq m) and is part of Morya Grand, a ready-to-move commercial project developed by Nakta Investment Pvt Ltd, spread across 0.69 acres.

news.title: Government plans zero-collateral housing loans for low and middle-income groups
news.para: Amendments to the Credit Risk Guarantee Fund Scheme for Low-Income Housing (CRGFTLIH) are being examined to pave the way for the scheme, they said, adding that the loan could have a tenure of 30 years.

news.title: Private equity investment in Indian real estate up 32% in 2024 to $4.15 billion: Report
news.para: Real estate consultant Knight Frank India on Thursday released a report 'Trends in Private Equity Investment in India 2024'.

news.title: Groundwater levels in Noida drop by over 16 meters in six years
news.para: Officials said on Wednesday that the district groundwater department had installed digital piezometers at seven areas across Noida to calculate groundwater levels before and after monsoon.

news.title: Gorakhpur civic body demolishes illegal structures in Khariya Pokhara
news.para: Accompanied by a heavy police contingent, the enforcement team demolished illegal structures in Shahpur area, against strong public resistance.

news.title: Delhi organization to protest for implementation of Land Pooling policy
news.para: According to a statement, Bhupender Bazad, president of the Delhi Master Plan Committee, has urged the government to notify the Master Plan Delhi 2041 and take concrete steps to implement the revised LPP and GDA policies.

news.title: US: Single-family housing rebounds in November 2024
news.para: The report from the Commerce Department on Wednesday showed only a slight increase last month in permits for the future construction of single-family homes, suggesting that residential investment will probably not contribute much to economic growth in the fourth quarter.

news.title: Kaisa shareholders approve $4.8 billion bond issue under restructuring plan
news.para: They have also approved the work fee share issue of around $26.9 million with Citicorp International, a bond trustee of an ad hoc group of bondholders, the company said.

news.title: Karnataka assembly clears bill to transform Muda into independent body
news.para: Once signed into an Act, Muda will become Mysuru Development Authority (MDA) and will be designed to better manage the Mysuru's rapid expansion and urban development.

news.title: Gujarat government revises land allocation policy for GIDC estates
news.para: Under the new system, three different slabs have been fixed for industrial estates, where land in less developed, moderately developed and developed estates will be provided at 100%, 125% and 150% respectively of the existing jantri rates.

news.title: NGT forms panel to ascertain facts about illegal extraction of groundwater in Delhi
news.para: The green body was hearing a plea claiming the two people, who were raising "huge" commercial constructions on Bungalow Road, were illegally extracting groundwater through borewells.
